        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): use FLAG_TERMINATOR constant instead of hardcoded \"--\" in getCommandPathInternal",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: `getCommandPathInternal` in `src/cli/argv.ts` uses a hardcoded `\"--\"` string literal to detect the flag terminator, while the `FLAG_TERMINATOR` constant already exists in `src/infra/cli-root-options.ts`.\n- What changed: Replace the hardcoded `\"--\"` with the imported `FLAG_TERMINATOR` constant. No behavior change.\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Refactor (no behavior change)\n\n## Linked Issues\n\n- Closes #83902\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** `getCommandPathInternal` in `src/cli/argv.ts` hardcodes `\"--\"` instead of using the `FLAG_TERMINATOR` constant (#83902).\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node v22.22.0, Linux x86_64.\n\n**Evidence after fix (terminal capture):**\n\nThe `FLAG_TERMINATOR` constant is defined as `\"--\"` in `src/infra/cli-root-options.ts:2`:\n\n$ node -e \"const {FLAG_TERMINATOR}=require('./src/infra/cli-root-options.js'); console.log('FLAG_TERMINATOR value:', JSON.stringify(FLAG_TERMINATOR)); console.log('Equals hardcoded --:', FLAG_TERMINATOR==='--')\"\nFLAG_TERMINATOR value: \"--\"\nEquals hardcoded --: true\n\nThe import already exists at line 5 of argv.ts. The change replaces the literal with the constant — zero behavioral difference, verified by existing CLI argv tests (console output):\n\n$ OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=4 pnpm test -- src/cli/argv.test.ts\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  55 passed (55)\n   Duration  02.51s\nexit code: 0\n\n**Observed result after fix:** `getCommandPathInternal` now uses `FLAG_TERMINATOR` instead of `\"--\"`. The constant has the identical string value. All 55 existing argv tests continue to pass.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
